Also implements BaseRenderingParameters_1377e6e44d0d4f588ade93076e9feb0d, BaseRenderingParameters, IDynamicPlaceholder, _PerSiteStandardValues, IStyling, IComponentVariant, GridParameters.

fields.name: allowCredentials
fields.description: The Access-Control-Allow-Credentials header indicates whether or not the response to the request can be exposed when the credentials flag is set to true.  When used as part of a response to a preflight request, this indicates whether or not the actual request can be made using credentials. Simple GET requests are not preflighted, and so if a request is made for a resource with credentials, if this header is not returned with the resource, the response is ignored by the browser and not returned to web content.

fields.name: allowHeaders
fields.description: The Access-Control-Allow-Headers header is used in response to a preflight request to indicate which HTTP headers can be used when making the actual request.

fields.name: allowMethods
fields.description: The Access-Control-Allow-Methods header specifies the method or methods allowed when accessing the resource. This is used in response to a preflight request.

fields.name: allowOrigin
fields.description: The origin parameter specifies a URI that may access the resource. The browser must enforce this. For requests without credentials, the server may specify "*" as a wildcard, thereby allowing any origin to access the resource.

fields.name: exposeHeaders
fields.description: The Access-Control-Expose-Headers header lets a server whitelist headers that browsers are allowed to access.

fields.name: maxAge
fields.description: The  Access-Control-Max-Age header indicates how long the results of a preflight request can be cached.
